Description: Body sherd of Chian, possibly Grand Style, pottery chalice with part of cul; discoloured white slip; interior: glazed streaky dark brown with added red and added white bands; exterior: above cul, dark red line at an angle above thin brown line; on cul, part of double guilloche band beside handle frill pattern; below, dark brown band; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: For parallels regarding the cul decoration, see Boston 88.1069.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0803) (phase 2)
